AGENDA OF THE EDUCATION AND SOCIAL WORK SOCIETY AGM 

1. Opening and Welcome
2. Apologies and leaves of absence.
3. Minutes of the previous meeting.
4. Business arising from the minutes
5. Correspondence.
6. Motions on Notice - Constitutional Amendments:
·         2.2.1.Foster a greater sense of community and collegiality amongst the members of the Faculty of Education and Social Work at the University of Sydney, hereinafter ‘the Faculty’, both professionally and socially; TO Foster a greater sense of community and collegiality amongst the members of the School of Education and Social Work at the University of Sydney, hereinafter ‘the School’, both professionally and socially;
·         2.2.2.Provide representation for Education and Social Work Students on Faculty Committees, communicating student concerns to the University, Faculty of Education and Social Work and other bodies; TO Provide representation for Education and Social Work Students on School Committees, communicating student concerns to the University, School of Education and Social Work and other bodies;
·         2.2.3.Work with the Faculty of Education and Social Work to provide opportunities for mentoring, recreation, sport and social interaction between Education and Social Work students; TO Work with the School of Education and Social Work to provide opportunities for mentoring, recreation, sport and social interaction between Education and Social Work students;
·         2.2.4.Offer guidance to students, in consultation with the Faculty of Education and Social Work as to career pathways and options available to students; and TO Offer guidance to students, in consultation with the School of Education and Social Work as to career pathways and options available to students; and
·         3.1.1.Ordinary Membership: All members of the Faculty of Education and Social Work at the University of Sydney be they members of the academic staff, undergraduate, postgraduate or honours students, shall be eligible for Ordinary Membership of the Society. Any Ordinary Member shall hold one vote at general meetings and elections of the Society at which they are present.TO Ordinary Membership: All Members of The University of Sydney Union shall be eligible for Ordinary Membership of the Society. Any Ordinary Member shall hold one vote at all meetings and elections of the Society at which they are present.
·         3.1.2.Alumni Membership: Persons who have graduated from the Faculty of Education and Social Work at the University of Sydney and its predecessor institutions including the Sydney Teachers College shall be eligible for Alumni Membership. Alumni Members are not eligible to hold Executive positions vote in elections or vote at meetings of the Society unless they qualify for Ordinary Membership of the Society. TO Associate Membership: All holders of a current Access Card of The University of Sydney Union other than those who qualify for Ordinary Membership shall be eligible for Associate Membership of the Society. Associate Members are not eligible to hold Executive positions, vote in elections or vote at meetings of the Society.
·         Delete 3.1.3., 3.1.4.
·         3.2.As the Society is considered a Faculty Society and membership is open to the entire student body and staff of the Faculty, no subscription fees shall be due in order to gain membership of the Society TO Upon payment of a subscription fee, a person shall be deemed an Ordinary Member or Associate Member of the Society and henceforth be bound by this Constitution.The subscription fees for membership shall be:
Ordinary Membership $3
Associate Membership $3
·         4.4.3.Student Representatives to sit on Faculty Committees, when requested by the Faculty of Education and Social Work; and TO  Student Representatives to sit on School Committees, when requested by the Faculty of Education and Social Work; and
·         4.7.1. In the Event that no such candidate is nominated, any student of the Faculty may cast their name for Election TO In the Event that no such candidate is nominated, any Member of the Society may cast their name for Election.
·         5.1.5.Liaise with the Faculty, the University of Sydney Union, the Clubs and Societies Office and any other parties; TO Liaise with the School, the University of Sydney Union, the Clubs and Societies Office and any other parties;
·         5.1.6.Call an Executive or General Meeting as he or she sees fit, in communication with the Executive to direct the Society and tend to any day-to-day issues; TO Call an Executive or General Meeting as they see fit, in communication with the Executive to direct the Society and tend to any day-to-day issues;
·         5.1.7.Represent the interests of the Students of the Society to the Faculty of Education and Social Work; TO Represent the interests of the Students of the Society to the School of Education and Social Work;
·         5.2.1.Liaise with student members of Faculty committees in the interest of Students and the Society; TO Liaise with student members of School Committees in the interest of Students and the Society;
·         5.2.2.Represent the interests of the Society’s Members at Faculty Committee or affiliated meetings; TO Represent the interests of the Society’s Members at School Committee or affiliated meetings;
·         5.2.3. Receive suggestions, concerns or issues from students and communicate these to relevant Student Representatives on Faculty Committees and Executives of the Society; TO Receive suggestions, concerns or issues from students and communicate these to relevant Student Representatives on School Committees and Executives of the Society;
·         5.3.2. Liaise with the Faculty Events, Scholarships and Careers Offices to advocate career opportunities for students; TO Liaise with the School Events, Scholarships and Careers Offices to advocate career opportunities for students;
·         5.3.3. Receive suggestions, concerns or issues from students and communicate these to relevant Student Representatives on Faculty Committees and Executives of the Society; TO Receive suggestions, concerns or issues from students and communicate these to relevant Student Representatives on School Committees and Executives of the Society;
·         5.8.1.Foster within the Faculty an awareness of the Society, the Society’s aims and the Society’s activities and work with the Events and Fundraising & Sponsorship Director to foster amongst members an awareness of the Society’s events; TO Foster within the School an awareness of the Society, the Society’s aims and the Society’s activities and work with the Events and Fundraising & Sponsorship Director to foster amongst members an awareness of the Society’s events;
·         5.10.1.Liaise with Students and the Faculty, in particular communication and fostering an awareness of Support Services available to Students; TO Liaise with Students and the School, in particular communication and fostering an awareness of Support Services available to Students;
·         5.10.2. Foster an atmosphere of equal opportunity and equality within the Society and throughout the Faculty; TO Foster an atmosphere of equal opportunity and equality within the Society and throughout the School;
·         5.10.3. Provide a point of contact for students in liaising with the Faculty. The Director shall direct students to appropriate academics or administration staff members as the need arises. Director may assist students, however academic advice is strictly prohibited; TO Provide a point of contact for students in liaising with the School. The Director shall direct students to appropriate academics or administration staff members as the need arises. Director may assist students, however academic advice is strictly prohibited;
·         5.13.1.Liaise with and communicate the initiatives of the Society to all undergraduate students in the Faculty; TO Liaise with and communicate the initiatives of the Society to all undergraduate students in the School;
·         5.13.2. Report consistently to the Executive, matters affecting Undergraduate student experience in the Faculty of Education and Social Work; TO Report consistently to the Executive, matters affecting Undergraduate student experience in the School of Education and Social Work;
·         5.14.1. Liaise with and communicate the initiatives of the Society to all Postgraduate students in the Faculty; TO Liaise with and communicate the initiatives of the Society to all Postgraduate students in the School;
·         5.14.2. Report consistently to the Executive, matters affecting Postgraduate student experience in the Faculty of Education and Social Work; TO Report consistently to the Executive, matters affecting Postgraduate student experience in the School of Education and Social Work;
·         5.15.1.Be a first year student studying in the Faculty of Education and Social Work; TO Be a first year student studying in the School of Education and Social Work;
·         5.15.2. Liaise with and communicate the initiatives of the Society to all first year students of the Faculty of Education and Social Work; TO Liaise with and communicate the initiatives of the Society to all first year students of the School of Education and Social Work;
·         5.15.3.Report consistently to the Executive, matters affecting First Year Student experience in the Faculty of Education and Social Work; TO Report consistently to the Executive, matters affecting First Year Student experience in the School of Education and Social Work;
·         5.15.4.Work and communicate with the First Year Experience Coordinator in the Faculty of Education and Social Work; and TO Work and communicate with the First Year Experience Coordinator in the School of Education and Social Work; and
·         5.16.1. Shall be a female identifying student from the Faculty of Education and Social Work; TO Shall be a female identifying student from the School of Education and Social Work;
·         5.16.2. Promote the interests of all female identifying students within the Faculty of Education and Social Work; TO Promote the interests of all female identifying students within the School of Education and Social Work;
·         5.16.4. Provide a perspective on creating and fostering a more gender inclusive community, both within the Faculty and the broader professions of Education and Social Work; and TO Provide a perspective on creating and fostering a more gender inclusive community, both within the School and the broader professions of Education and Social Work; and
·         5.17.1.Shall be a queer identifying student from the Faculty of Education and Social Work TO Shall be a queer identifying student from the School of Education and Social Work
